After skin preparation of right clavicular region on supine position , a 6 ml of 1 % lidocaine HCI was locally infiltrated . The right internal jugular vein was punctured with a micropucture needle under US - guidance and a microsheath was then introduced into superior vena cava over a 0.018 - inch hairwire . 1. Title Percutaneous Implantation of Infusion Port . right . 2. Procedure

After skin preparation of right clavicular region on supine position , a 6 ml of 1 % lidocaine HCI was locally infiltrated . The right internal jugular vein was punctured with a micropucture needle under US - guidance and a microsheath was then introduced into superior vena cava over a 0.018 - inch hairwire . The skin was incised and subcutaneous pocket & tunnel was prepared by dissection . After dilation , an infusion port with catheter was inserted over a guidewire and a peel - away sheath . The tip of the catheter was adjusted at the atriocaval junction and the infusion port was filled with a 10 ml of saline solution mixed with Heparin 1.000 units for locking . The incision site was closed by applying tissue adhesive . The patient tolerated the procedure well and no immediate complication developed . [ CONCLUSION ]
Uncomplicated implantation of infusion port via right transjugular venous approach under US & fluoroscopy . [ RECOMMENDATION ]
